In her first interview since returning from Ethiopia, where she was head of the African Union, Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma said she will strive to unify the ANC - if nominated to run for the presidency. The interview, which was published in The Star, highlights Dlamini-Zuma's aversion towards patriarchy and her animosity toward claims that her ex-husband, President Jacob Zuma, is supporting her. Here are three significant things that should be noted from Dlamini-Zuma's interview:  Dlamini-Zuma will deliver the memorial lecture for ANC struggle stalwart Steven Dlamini on Tuesday. The event takes place in the Harry Gwala region in KwaZulu-Natal at 2pm.